headline: Corteva beats first-quarter profit estimates on higher seed pricing
summary: The results come as the agrichemical industry braces itself against a potential fallout from U.S. President Donald Trump's trade policy.  Corteva said it continues to expect current-year net sales of $17.2 billion to $17.6 billion, but added the outlook did not reflect the impact of tariffs.  In the seed segment, Corteva said prices rose 3% in most regions, led by North America.
